---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="What Size Shipping Container Do You Need? | Steel Box Direct"
  description="Figure out the right container size for your needs. Compare 20ft, 40ft, and 40ft high cube containers with dimensions, use cases, and our interactive calculator."
  pageType="guide"
  guideTopic="size"
>
  <div class="guide-header">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="sh">
        <span class="idx">§ 01</span>
        <span class="nm">Decision: Size</span>
        <span class="tg">ISO 668 Standards</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="big">Right Size =<br><em>Perfect Fit.</em></h1>
      <p class="guide-lede">
        Size is the first decision—get it wrong and your equipment won't fit or you'll pay for space you don't need.
        A 20-foot container fits one tractor. A 40-foot holds farm equipment, workshop tools, or business inventory.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="guide-content">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="main-col">
          <h2>The Three Standard Sizes</h2>
          <p>Shipping containers were built for international cargo, so dimensions are standardized worldwide. A "20-foot container" is the same size whether it comes from our yard or anywhere else.</p>

          <div class="size-card" style="border-left-color: var(--c1-size);">
            <h3>20-Foot Container</h3>
            <div class="specs">
              <div class="spec-bit"><span class="lbl">Interior</span><span class="val">19'4" × 7'8" × 7'10"</span></div>
              <div class="spec-bit"><span class="lbl">Floor Space</span><span class="val">~160 sq ft</span></div>
            </div>
            <p><strong>Perfect for:</strong> One tractor + attachment storage, horse trailers, or a small workshop.</p>
            <div class="tag-row"><span class="m">→ Tom · 40-ft primary</span></div>
          </div>

          <div class="size-card" style="border-left-color: var(--c3-deliver);">
            <h3>40-Foot Container</h3>
            <div class="specs">
              <div class="spec-bit"><span class="lbl">Interior</span><span class="val">39'5" × 7'8" × 7'10"</span></div>
              <div class="spec-bit"><span class="lbl">Floor Space</span><span class="val">~320 sq ft</span></div>
            </div>
            <p><strong>Perfect for:</strong> Complete farm equipment lineup, multiple vehicles, or business inventory.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="size-card" style="border-left-color: var(--c5-permits);">
            <h3>40-Foot High Cube</h3>
            <div class="specs">
              <div class="spec-bit"><span class="lbl">Interior</span><span class="val">39'5" × 7'8" × 8'10"</span></div>
              <div class="spec-bit"><span class="lbl">Floor Space</span><span class="val">~320 sq ft</span></div>
            </div>
            <p><strong>The extra 12" height:</strong> Fits tall equipment like combines or stacked inventory.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="sidebar-col">
          <div class="authority-card">
            <div class="m">Key Statistics</div>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>73%</strong> of farm operations store equipment year-round.</li>
              <li><strong>1 in 3</strong> buyers initially choose the wrong size.</li>
              <li><strong>40-ft</strong> costs 30% less per cubic foot than two 20-ft units.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div class="cta-card">
            <h4>Still unsure?</h4>
            <p>Use our interactive tool to get a recommendation.</p>
            <a href="/size/calculator/" class="btn">Open Calculator <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 12h14M13 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg></a>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .guide-header {
      background: var(--yellow);
      padding: 80px 0 64px;
      border-bottom: 2.5px solid var(--ink);
    }
    .guide-lede {
      font-size: 22px;
      line-height: 1.45;
      margin: 40px 0 0;
      max-width: 720px;
      font-weight: 500;
    }

    .guide-content {
      padding: 96px 0;
      background: var(--cream);
    }

    .row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1.5fr 1fr;
      gap: 80px;
      align-items: start;
    }

    .size-card {
      background: white;
      border: 2px solid var(--ink);
      border-left: 8px solid var(--ink);
      padding: 32px;
      margin-top: 40px;
      box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--ink);
    }
    .size-card h3 {
      font-family: var(--narrow);
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 28px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .specs {
      display: flex;
      gap: 32px;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      padding-bottom: 20px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(11,15,26,.1);
    }
    .spec-bit .lbl {
      display: block;
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 11px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      opacity: .5;
    }
    .spec-bit .val {
      font-family: var(--narrow);
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 20px;
    }

    .authority-card {
      background: var(--ink);
      color: var(--cream);
      padding: 32px;
      border: 2px solid var(--ink);
    }
    .authority-card .m { color: var(--yellow); margin-bottom: 16px; }
    .authority-card ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
    .authority-card li { margin-bottom: 16px; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.45; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(246,241,231,.1); padding-bottom: 16px; }
    .authority-card li:last-child { border: none; }

    .cta-card {
      margin-top: 40px;
      background: white;
      border: 2px solid var(--ink);
      padding: 32px;
      box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--c5-permits);
    }
    .cta-card h4 { font-family: var(--narrow); font-size: 24px; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .cta-card p { font-size: 15px; margin-bottom: 20px; }

    @media (max-width: 960px) {
      .row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 48px; }
      .guide-header { padding: 48px 0; }
      .big { font-size: clamp(48px, 10vw, 80px); }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>